	<entry>
		<title>Construction Cost Estimation: Challenges and Issues</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://www.methvin.org/construction-cost-estimation-challenges-and-issues"/>
		<published>2013-03-19T19:52:57+00:00</published>
		<updated>2013-03-19T19:52:57+00:00</updated>
		<id>http://www.methvin.org/construction-cost-estimation-challenges-and-issues</id>
		<author>
			<name>Richard Gush</name>
			<email>richard.gush@methvin.org</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;With every new project comes a new specification and relating challenges since there are hardly any projects that are similar in all aspects. The construction and project management industry, like other trades, has to each, his own. Every patron comes up with exclusive designs in mind, thereby making the project inimitably different. This can prove to be a considerable saddle for the estimators, as it requires them to precisely draw a project estimate and justify all the crucial activities of delivery. Construction cost estimators are highly conversant and acquainted with every division of construction estimation technique, from outsourcing of material to labour service.&lt;/p&gt;
</summary>
